**1. System Overview**

POGLS V3.4 is a binary storage engine based on angular addressing. The
core law is:

**A = floor( θ × 2ⁿ )**

Where n=20 by default, giving 1,048,576 unique addresses. All offset
arithmetic uses bit-shift only --- no multiply/divide in hot paths.

**1.1 Architecture Layers**

