**12. Tails --- Shadow Log & Emergency Key**

Tails is a passive stalker component that runs anti-parallel to the main
pointer. It has zero write access to the core system. Its sole purpose
is to log abnormality events and hold a last-known-good state for
emergency recovery.

**12.1 Design**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Property**                        **Value**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Direction                           Runs at opposite angle: address =
                                      (MAX − pointer_address)

  Storage                             Uses HoneycombSlot reserved space
                                      (pogls_honeycomb_init --- currently
                                      no-op in C core)

  Access rights                       NONE --- read + log only. No write
                                      path anywhere.

  Activation                          Passive always. 1 exception:
                                      pointer crash/corruption → provides
                                      emergency key

  Core file                           binary-index.js (Node.js,
                                      standalone)

  Tests                               test-binary-index.js --- 52/52 PASS
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**12.2 What Tails Stores**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Data**                            **Purpose**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  DNA hash per file version (MD5 or   Deduplication + identity
  SHA-256)                            fingerprint

  algoId per entry                    Safe MD5→SHA-256 migration without
                                      false duplicates

  Abnormality events                  Logged silently --- never forwarded
                                      to core

  Merkle root at immigration boundary Snapshot seal for integrity proof

  Migration state                     Crash-safe hash upgrade, resumable
  (IDLE/RUNNING/COMMITTED)            
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**12.3 Emergency Key --- 1 Active Case**

If the main pointer crashes or its state is unrecoverable, Tails can
provide:

-   Last committed Merkle root before crash

-   DNA hashes of all known-good versions

-   Migration state snapshot (to resume or revert)

This is a read-only handoff --- Tails never initiates recovery itself.
It only provides the data; a human or orchestrator decides what to do
with it.

**12.4 Relationship to Core**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
                  **Tails**
  --------------- -------------------------------------------------------
  Reads WAL       ❌ No

  Reads Snapshot  ❌ No

  Reads           ❌ No
  Hydra/Audit     

  Writes anywhere ❌ Never

  Uses            ✅ Reserved space only
  HoneycombSlot   

  Affects core    ❌ Zero impact
  tests           

  Language        Node.js (binary-index.js)
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

